type():
it is predefined function.it is used check your variable or literal which type.
a=10
b=2.5
c="hi"
print(type(a))
print(type(b))
print(type(c))
print(type(True))

<class 'int'>
<class 'float'>
<class 'str'>
<class 'bool'>

id():it is predeined function .it is used to show refernce or address variable, literal.

a=10
b=2.5
print(id(a),a)
print(id(b),b)

140720976300760 10
2000900959344 2.5


